{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Who are we?"},{"time":2000,"text":"That is the big question."},{"time":4000,"text":"And essentially we are just an upright-walking, big-brained,"},{"time":10000,"text":"super-intelligent ape."},{"time":12000,"text":"This could be us."},{"time":14000,"text":"We belong to the family called the Hominidae."},{"time":17000,"text":"We are the species called Homo sapiens sapiens,"},{"time":21000,"text":"and it's important to remember that,"},{"time":23000,"text":"in terms of our place in the world today"},{"time":26000,"text":"and our future on planet Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29000,"text":"We are one species"},{"time":33000,"text":"of about five and a half thousand mammalian species"},{"time":37000,"text":"that exist on planet Earth today."},{"time":39000,"text":"And that's just a tiny fraction of all species"},{"time":42000,"text":"that have ever lived on the planet in past times."},{"time":46000,"text":"We're one species out of approximately,"},{"time":49000,"text":"or let's say, at least 16 upright-walking apes"},{"time":53000,"text":"that have existed over the past six to eight million years."},{"time":56000,"text":"But as far as we know, we're the only upright-walking ape"},{"time":59000,"text":"that exists on planet Earth today, except for the bonobos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62000,"text":"And it's important to remember that,"},{"time":64000,"text":"because the bonobos are so human,"},{"time":66000,"text":"and they share 99 percent of their genes with us."},{"time":71000,"text":"And we share our origins with a handful of the living great apes."},{"time":75000,"text":"It's important to remember that we evolved."},{"time":79000,"text":"Now, I know that's a dirty word for some people,"},{"time":81000,"text":"but we evolved from common ancestors"},{"time":86000,"text":"with the gorillas, the chimpanzee and also the bonobos."},{"time":96000,"text":"We have a common past, and we have a common future."},{"time":100000,"text":"And it is important to remember that all of these great apes"},{"time":105000,"text":"have come on as long and as interesting evolutionary journey"},{"time":110000,"text":"as we ourselves have today."},{"time":113000,"text":"And it's this journey that is of such interest to humanity,"},{"time":117000,"text":"and it's this journey that has been the focus"},{"time":120000,"text":"of the past three generations of my family,"},{"time":123000,"text":"as we've been in East Africa looking for the fossil remains"},{"time":126000,"text":"of our ancestors to try and piece together our evolutionary past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"And this is how we look for them."},{"time":133000,"text":"A group of dedicated young men and women walk very slowly"},{"time":138000,"text":"out across vast areas of Africa,"},{"time":141000,"text":"looking for small fragments of bone, fossil bone, that may be on the surface."},{"time":148000,"text":"And that's an example of what we may do as we walk across"},{"time":152000,"text":"the landscape in Northern Kenya, looking for fossils."},{"time":155000,"text":"I doubt many of you in the audience can see"},{"time":158000,"text":"the fossil that's in this picture,"},{"time":161000,"text":"but if you look very carefully, there is a jaw, a lower jaw,"},{"time":164000,"text":"of a 4.1-million-year-old upright-walking ape"},{"time":167000,"text":"as it was found at Lake Turkana on the west side."},{"time":171000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":174000,"text":"It's extremely time-consuming, labor-intensive"},{"time":177000,"text":"and it is something that is going to involve a lot more people,"},{"time":181000,"text":"to begin to piece together our past."},{"time":184000,"text":"We still really haven't got a very complete picture of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187000,"text":"When we find a fossil, we mark it."},{"time":191000,"text":"Today, we've got great technology: we have GPS."},{"time":194000,"text":"We mark it with a GPS fix,"},{"time":196000,"text":"and we also take a digital photograph of the specimen,"},{"time":200000,"text":"so we could essentially put it back on the surface,"},{"time":203000,"text":"exactly where we found it."},{"time":205000,"text":"And we can bring all this information into big GIS packages, today."},{"time":209000,"text":"When we then find something very important,"},{"time":213000,"text":"like the bones of a human ancestor,"},{"time":215000,"text":"we begin to excavate it extremely carefully and slowly,"},{"time":219000,"text":"using dental picks and fine paintbrushes."},{"time":222000,"text":"And all the sediment is then put through these screens,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and where we go again through it very carefully,"},{"time":227000,"text":"looking for small bone fragments, and it's then washed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231000,"text":"And these things are so exciting. They are so often the only,"},{"time":235000,"text":"or the very first time that anybody has ever seen the remains."},{"time":240000,"text":"And here's a very special moment, when my mother and myself"},{"time":243000,"text":"were digging up some remains of human ancestors."},{"time":249000,"text":"And it is one of the most special things"},{"time":251000,"text":"to ever do with your mother."},{"time":253000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":257000,"text":"Not many people can say that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"But now, let me take you back to Africa, two million years ago."},{"time":266000,"text":"I'd just like to point out, if you look at the map of Africa,"},{"time":271000,"text":"it does actually look like a hominid skull in its shape."},{"time":280000,"text":"Now we're going to go to the East African and the Rift Valley."},{"time":284000,"text":"It essentially runs up from the Gulf of Aden,"},{"time":287000,"text":"or runs down to Lake Malawi."},{"time":291000,"text":"And the Rift Valley is a depression."},{"time":293000,"text":"It's a basin, and rivers flow down from the highlands into the basin,"},{"time":300000,"text":"carrying sediment, preserving the bones of animals that lived there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304000,"text":"If you want to become a fossil, you actually need to die somewhere"},{"time":308000,"text":"where your bones will be rapidly buried."},{"time":310000,"text":"You then hope that the earth moves in such a way"},{"time":312000,"text":"as to bring the bones back up to the surface."},{"time":315000,"text":"And then you hope that one of us lot"},{"time":318000,"text":"will walk around and find small pieces of you."},{"time":321000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":322000,"text":"OK, so it is absolutely surprising that we know as much"},{"time":325000,"text":"as we do know today about our ancestors,"},{"time":328000,"text":"because it's incredibly difficult,"},{"time":330000,"text":"A, for these things to become -- to be -- preserved,"},{"time":333000,"text":"and secondly, for them to have been brought back up to the surface."},{"time":336000,"text":"And we really have only spent 50 years looking for these remains,"},{"time":341000,"text":"and begin to actually piece together our evolutionary story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"So, let's go to Lake Turkana, which is one such lake basin"},{"time":349000,"text":"in the very north of our country, Kenya."},{"time":351000,"text":"And if you look north here, there's a big river that flows into the lake"},{"time":355000,"text":"that's been carrying sediment and preserving the remains"},{"time":358000,"text":"of the animals that lived there."},{"time":360000,"text":"Fossil sites run up and down both lengths of that lake basin,"},{"time":364000,"text":"which represents some 20,000 square miles."},{"time":369000,"text":"That's a huge job that we've got on our hands."},{"time":371000,"text":"Two million years ago at Lake Turkana,"},{"time":375000,"text":"Homo erectus, one of our human ancestors,"},{"time":378000,"text":"actually lived in this region."},{"time":380000,"text":"You can see some of the major fossil sites that we've been working"},{"time":383000,"text":"in the north. But, essentially, two million years ago,"},{"time":388000,"text":"Homo erectus, up in the far right corner,"},{"time":391000,"text":"lived alongside three other species of human ancestor."},{"time":399000,"text":"And here is a skull of a Homo erectus,"},{"time":402000,"text":"which I just pulled off the shelf there."},{"time":404000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":408000,"text":"But it is not to say that being a single species on planet Earth is the norm."},{"time":414000,"text":"In fact, if you go back in time,"},{"time":416000,"text":"it is the norm that there are multiple species of hominids"},{"time":421000,"text":"or of human ancestors that coexist at any one time."},{"time":423000,"text":"Where did these things come from?"},{"time":426000,"text":"That's what we're still trying to find answers to,"},{"time":429000,"text":"and it is important to realize that there is diversity"},{"time":433000,"text":"in all different species, and our ancestors are no exception."},{"time":439000,"text":"Here's some reconstructions of some of the fossils"},{"time":445000,"text":"that have been found from Lake Turkana."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448000,"text":"But I was very lucky to have been brought up in Kenya,"},{"time":451000,"text":"essentially accompanying my parents to Lake Turkana"},{"time":455000,"text":"in search of human remains."},{"time":457000,"text":"And we were able to dig up, when we got old enough,"},{"time":460000,"text":"fossils such as this, a slender-snouted crocodile."},{"time":465000,"text":"And we dug up giant tortoises, and elephants and things like that."},{"time":469000,"text":"But when I was 12, as I was in this picture,"},{"time":471000,"text":"a very exciting expedition was in place on the west side,"},{"time":475000,"text":"when they found essentially the skeleton of this Homo erectus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482000,"text":"I could relate to this Homo erectus skeleton very well,"},{"time":486000,"text":"because I was the same age that he was when he died."},{"time":492000,"text":"And I imagined him to be tall, dark-skinned."},{"time":496000,"text":"His brothers certainly were able to run long distances"},{"time":501000,"text":"chasing prey, probably sweating heavily as they did so."},{"time":504000,"text":"He was very able to use stones effectively as tools."},{"time":509000,"text":"And this individual himself, this one that I'm holding up here,"},{"time":513000,"text":"actually had a bad back. He'd probably had an injury as a child."},{"time":518000,"text":"He had a scoliosis and therefore must have been looked after"},{"time":522000,"text":"quite carefully by other female, and probably much smaller,"},{"time":526000,"text":"members of his family group, to have got to where he did in life, age 12."},{"time":532000,"text":"Unfortunately for him, he fell into a swamp"},{"time":535000,"text":"and couldn't get out."},{"time":537000,"text":"Essentially, his bones were rapidly buried"},{"time":540000,"text":"and beautifully preserved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542000,"text":"And he remained there until 1.6 million years later,"},{"time":547000,"text":"when this very famous fossil hunter, Kamoya Kimeu,"},{"time":551000,"text":"walked along a small hillside"},{"time":554000,"text":"and found that small piece of his skull lying on the surface"},{"time":558000,"text":"amongst the pebbles, recognized it as being hominid."},{"time":564000,"text":"It's actually this little piece up here on the top."},{"time":566000,"text":"Well, an excavation was begun immediately,"},{"time":570000,"text":"and more and more little bits of skull"},{"time":572000,"text":"started to be extracted from the sediment."},{"time":576000,"text":"And what was so fun about it was this:"},{"time":578000,"text":"the skull pieces got closer and closer to the roots of the tree,"},{"time":584000,"text":"and fairly recently the tree had grown up,"},{"time":586000,"text":"but it had found that the skull had captured nice water in the hillside,"},{"time":591000,"text":"and so it had decided to grow its roots in and around this,"},{"time":594000,"text":"holding it in place and preventing it from washing away down the slope."},{"time":599000,"text":"We began to find limb bones; we found finger bones,"},{"time":604000,"text":"the bones of the pelvis, vertebrae, ribs, the collar bones,"},{"time":607000,"text":"things that had never, ever been seen before in Homo erectus."},{"time":612000,"text":"It was truly exciting."},{"time":614000,"text":"He had a body very similar to our own,"},{"time":619000,"text":"and he was on the threshold of becoming human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"Well, shortly afterwards, members of his species"},{"time":627000,"text":"started to move northwards out of Africa,"},{"time":630000,"text":"and you start to see fossils of Homo erectus"},{"time":633000,"text":"in Georgia, China and also in parts of Indonesia."},{"time":639000,"text":"So, Homo erectus was the first human ancestor to leave Africa"},{"time":644000,"text":"and begin its spread across the globe."},{"time":646000,"text":"Some exciting finds, again, as I mentioned,"},{"time":651000,"text":"from Dmanisi, in the Republic of Georgia."},{"time":654000,"text":"But also, surprising finds"},{"time":656000,"text":"recently announced from the Island of Flores in Indonesia,"},{"time":659000,"text":"where a group of these human ancestors have been isolated,"},{"time":664000,"text":"and have become dwarfed, and they're only about a meter in height."},{"time":668000,"text":"But they lived only 18,000 years ago,"},{"time":672000,"text":"and that is truly extraordinary to think about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675000,"text":"Just to put this in terms of generations,"},{"time":678000,"text":"because people do find it hard to think of time,"},{"time":680000,"text":"Homo erectus left Africa 90,000 generations ago."},{"time":685000,"text":"We evolved essentially from an African stock."},{"time":688000,"text":"Again, at about 200,000 years as a fully-fledged us."},{"time":693000,"text":"And we only left Africa about 70,000 years ago."},{"time":697000,"text":"And until 30,000 years ago, at least three upright-walking apes"},{"time":702000,"text":"shared the planet Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704000,"text":"The question now is, well, who are we?"},{"time":707000,"text":"We're certainly a polluting, wasteful, aggressive species,"},{"time":712000,"text":"with a few nice things thrown in, perhaps."},{"time":715000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":716000,"text":"For the most part, we're not particularly pleasant at all."},{"time":722000,"text":"We have a much larger brain than our ape ancestors."},{"time":725000,"text":"Is this a good evolutionary adaptation, or is it going to lead us"},{"time":731000,"text":"to being the shortest-lived hominid species on planet Earth?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"And what is it that really makes us us?"},{"time":739000,"text":"I think it's our collective intelligence."},{"time":741000,"text":"It's our ability to write things down,"},{"time":744000,"text":"our language and our consciousness."},{"time":746000,"text":"From very primitive beginnings, with a very crude tool kit of stones,"},{"time":753000,"text":"we now have a very advanced tool kit, and our tool use"},{"time":758000,"text":"has really reached unprecedented levels:"},{"time":761000,"text":"we've got buggies to Mars; we've mapped the human genome;"},{"time":765000,"text":"and recently even created synthetic life, thanks to Craig Venter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"And we've also managed to communicate with people"},{"time":773000,"text":"all over the world, from extraordinary places."},{"time":776000,"text":"Even from within an excavation in northern Kenya,"},{"time":780000,"text":"we can talk to people about what we're doing."},{"time":782000,"text":"As Al Gore so clearly has reminded us,"},{"time":786000,"text":"we have reached extraordinary numbers"},{"time":790000,"text":"of people on this planet."},{"time":792000,"text":"Human ancestors really only survive on planet Earth,"},{"time":795000,"text":"if you look at the fossil record,"},{"time":797000,"text":"for about, on average, a million years at a time."},{"time":800000,"text":"We've only been around for the past 200,000 years as a species,"},{"time":804000,"text":"yet we've reached a population of more than six and a half billion people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809000,"text":"And last year, our population grew by 80 million."},{"time":812000,"text":"I mean, these are extraordinary numbers."},{"time":815000,"text":"You can see here, again, taken from Al Gore's book."},{"time":820000,"text":"But what's happened is our technology"},{"time":822000,"text":"has removed the checks and balances on our population growth."},{"time":827000,"text":"We have to control our numbers, and I think this is as important"},{"time":831000,"text":"as anything else that's being done in the world today."},{"time":833000,"text":"But we have to control our numbers,"},{"time":835000,"text":"because we can't really hold it together as a species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840000,"text":"My father so appropriately put it,"},{"time":843000,"text":"that \"We are certainly the only animal that makes conscious choices"},{"time":847000,"text":"that are bad for our survival as a species.\""},{"time":849000,"text":"Can we hold it together?"},{"time":855000,"text":"It's important to remember that we all evolved in Africa."},{"time":859000,"text":"We all have an African origin."},{"time":863000,"text":"We have a common past and we share a common future."},{"time":867000,"text":"Evolutionarily speaking, we're just a blip."},{"time":871000,"text":"We're sitting on the edge of a precipice,"},{"time":874000,"text":"and we have the tools and the technology at our hands"},{"time":881000,"text":"to communicate what needs to be done"},{"time":883000,"text":"to hold it together today."},{"time":887000,"text":"We could tell every single human being out there, if we really wanted to."},{"time":890000,"text":"But will we do that, or will we just let nature take its course?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":897000,"text":"Well, to end on a very positive note,"},{"time":900000,"text":"I think evolutionarily speaking,"},{"time":902000,"text":"this is probably a fairly good thing, in the end."},{"time":905000,"text":"I'll leave it at that, thank you very much."},{"time":907000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}